cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper proposes a network architecture for efficient scene understanding, which involves tasks such as semantic segmentation and instance segmentation. These tasks are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. The paper also introduces a novel network design, which can be considered a contribution to machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the proposed network can be applied to robotics (cs.RO) and computer graphics (cs.CR) domains, as scene understanding is important for both fields.
